{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"A Tech Blog","author":"Aidan Breen"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"60764cf7-1e52-5de9-874c-43c717559da3","excerpt":"I am taking control! Yes, I have made the leap and now control my own content here, on my own self-hosted blog. Do you like what I’ve done with the place? It…","html":"<blockquote>\n<p>I am taking control! Yes, I have made the leap and now control my own content here, on my own self-hosted blog. Do you like what I’ve done with the place?</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>It hasn’t all been roses, and I intend to cover the complications in a future post, but for the most part I feel confident in my decision to move away from Medium. There is however, one thing that I feel I am missing.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b90d9d35c2f6fa2a21da0b8e256cdbc1/66e30/image2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 80px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 105%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Applause button\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/b90d9d35c2f6fa2a21da0b8e256cdbc1/66e30/image2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b90d9d35c2f6fa2a21da0b8e256cdbc1/66e30/image2.png 80w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 80px) 100vw, 80px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Applause.</h2>\n<p>This is the <strong>applause</strong> feature, created by <a href=\"http://www.medium.com\">Medium</a>. It works kind of like Facebook’s <em>like</em> button, except you can click it multiple times. It’s dead simple, and it improves the user experience for everybody:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The author gets clear, purposeful feedback on their content.</li>\n<li>The reader gets a fun and flexible way to interact with the post.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/525cf/image1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 37.95233892321271%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"Applause in action\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/40fad/image1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/707e9/image1.png 148w,\n/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/649e0/image1.png 295w,\n/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/40fad/image1.png 590w,\n/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/b3fef/image1.png 885w,\n/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/301c0/image1.png 1180w,\n/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/b5a53/image1.png 1770w,\n/static/195dfa1432785b46d69355089a09ed5d/525cf/image1.png 2266w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    \n<em>Applause in action…barely</em></p>\n<p>The value of allowing readers to click it multiple times is clear as soon as you read something you <em>really</em> like. Click 10 times, and all of a sudden you feel empowered. Expressing the scale of your enjoyment goes  along way. It really does feel like applauding.</p>\n<h2>What about self hosted blogs?</h2>\n<p>jhgjh</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"The Case for Applause","date":"February 15, 2019"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/case-for-applause/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/vivisection-of-opentable-widget/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Vivisection of OpenTable widget.","draft":false}},"next":null}}